    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="751"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d751">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.1211/265</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the Division of Far Eastern Affairs</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hornbeck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of the Division of Mexican
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-25">November 25,
                            1933</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Johnson</hi>: Taking into consideration a large number
                    of factors, and giving special weight to the fact that the tension between the
                    United States and Japan has been substantially diminished during the past six
                    months and seems in a fair way to further diminution, <pb facs="0927" n="839"
                        xml:id="pg_839"/> I feel that we should take no steps whatever with regard
                    to the matter reported upon in the papers hereunder<note n="54"
                        xml:id="d751fn54">i. e., despatch No. 2255, February 7, from the Ambassador
                        in Mexico, <ref target="#pg_830">p. 830</ref>.</note> except to keep the
                    record of everything relating to it strictly confidential (but not to be
                    forgotten).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">tanley</hi>] K. H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >ornbeck</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
